description:
Debbie was a girls' comic launched by D.C. Thomson on 17th February 1973. As with most British girls' comics, it contained a mixture of comic strips and photo stories, and covered a broad range of genres, from romance to science fiction, horror and suspense to period drama, humour to superhero, all appearing alongside one another. One of the more successful girls' titles, it lasted for five hundred and eighteen issues, the final one coming out on the week of 15th January 1983, nearly a decade after the first issue. In 1978, during this lengthy run, Debbie absorbed Spellbound.

Part of a group of four sister titles for girls. The names of the four titles are Bunty, Judy, Mandy and Debbie. Each title had an accompanying weekly, monthly, and annual volume:

Bunty

  • Weekly: Bunty
  • Monthly: Bunty Picture Story Library for Girls
  • Annual: Bunty Annual

Debbie

  • Monthly: Debbie Picture Story Library For Girls
  • Annual: Debbie For Girls Annual

Judy

  • Weekly: Judy
  • Monthly: Judy Picture Story Library For Girls
  • Annual: Judy For Girls Annual

Mandy

  • Weekly: Mandy
  • Monthly: Mandy Picture Story Library For Girls
  • Annual: Mandy For Girls Annual
name: Debbie
